The Carbon Neutrality Coalition (CNC) is a group of countries, cities and organisations who have committed to take concrete and ambitious action to achieve the aims of the [[Paris Agreement]].<ref name=ccc4new>{{cite web|url=http://constructionclimatechallenge.com/2018/09/28/carbon-neutrality-coalition-net-zero-emissions-expands-19-countries/|title=Carbon Neutrality Coalition for net-zero emissions expands to 19 countries|accessdate=29 September 2018|date=2018-09-28}}</ref><ref name="iisdFirstMeetingNewMembers">{{cite web |title=Carbon Neutrality Coalition Convenes Inaugural Meeting, Welcomes New Members |url=http://sdg.iisd.org/news/carbon-neutrality-coalition-convenes-inaugural-meeting-welcomes-new-members/ |accessdate=24 November 2018}}</ref><ref name="utilityWeekUK">{{cite web |title=Policy & regulation UK joins worldwide coalition for ‘net zero’ emissions target |url=https://utilityweek.co.uk/uk-joins-worldwide-coalition-for-net-zero-emissions-target/ |accessdate=24 November 2018}}</ref>.  

==History==
The CNC was founded in 2017 by 16 countries and 32 cities<ref name=riInitial>{{cite web|url=https://resilienceintel.org/2017/12/14/one-planet-summit-12-transformational-commitments/|title=One Planet Summit: Transformational Commitments|accessdate=29 September 2018|date=2017-12-14}}</ref>.  In December New Zealand Climate Change Minister James Shaw said<ref name="beehiveNZ">{{cite web |title=Clear message on clean energy at OnePlanet Summit |url=https://www.beehive.govt.nz/release/clear-message-clean-energy-oneplanet-summit |accessdate=24 November 2018}}</ref>:

{{quotation
|
“The Coalition is a perfect fit with our goal of becoming a net zero emission economy by 2050”
}}

In September 2018 the Coalition held its first meeting at the [[UN General Assembly]]<ref name="iisdFirstMeetingNewMembers" /> and 4 new countries joined: the UK; Canada; Denmark and Spain<ref name=ccn4new>{{cite web|url=http://www.climatechangenews.com/2018/09/28/19-countries-team-go-carbon-neutral/|title=19 countries team up to go carbon neutral|accessdate=29 September 2018|date=2018-09-28}}</ref><ref name=bg4new>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessgreen.com/bg/news/3063559/net-zero-uk-joins-global-carbon-neutral-drive/|title=Net Zero: UK joins global 'carbon neutral' drive|accessdate=29 September 2018|date=2018-09-27}}</ref><ref name="utilityWeekUK" /><ref name="lamoncloaSpain">{{cite web |title=Pedro Sánchez announces that Spain will sign up to the carbon neutrality coalition as expression of its commitment in fight against climate change |url=http://www.lamoncloa.gob.es/lang/en/presidente/news/Paginas/2018/20180926-bloomberg.aspx |accessdate=24 November 2018}}</ref>.

==Benefits==
The coalition aims to achieve benefits in 3 key areas<ref name="iisdFirstMeetingNewMembers" />: 
* Socioeconomic benefits 
* Climate-resilient economies
* Accelerating global climate action

==Plan of Action==
Coalition members agree to
* Develop and share their de-carbonisation strategies, experiences, data and tools before 2020<ref name=ccc4new />
* Promote increased ambition from all countries globally on reducing emissions<ref name=ccc4new />

